  "reason_thou": "### 1. Understanding the Issue\nThe crash occurs due to an assertion
failure in `llvm::DataLayout::getTypeSizeInBits`, which checks if the type is sized. The
assertion fails because the type being passed is `VoidTyID`, which is not a sized
type.\n\n### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log\nFrom the `opt` log, the issue arises during the SLP
vectorization pass when analyzing a store chain. Specifically, the `store i32 %i4, ptr %i1,
align 4` instruction is being processed, and its type is being queried. The type of the
user (`U`) is `VoidTyID`, which is invalid for size computation.\n\n### 3. Root Cause
Analysis\nThe root cause is that the code does not properly handle cases where the type of
a user (`U`) is `VoidTyID`. This leads to an invalid call to `getTypeSizeInBits` on an
unsized type. The issue originates in the lambda function at line 16067 in
